The paper focuses on texture understanding and recognition using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new dataset for benchmarking texture recognition algorithms, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning models and their efficiency and generalization properties suggest that the paper could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the transferability of features from one domain to another, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR).
